        <module id="noun-other">
            <h lang="en">other</h>
            <h lang="gd">eile</h>
            <p lang="en">Examples from Gairm – <xl id="noun-other-gairm-xs">
                    <li>
                        <gd>Anns na ràithean ’s na bliadhnachan a tha air thoiseach oirnn, tha fhios
                            gun dig iomadh atharrachadh air Roinn na Gàidhlig sa’ Bh.B.C. Dh’ fhàg
                            Eóghan Mac-a- phì <m>a sheula fhéin</m> air an Roinn sin, agus air a’
                            Bh.B.C. an Albainn gu h-iomlan, agus air dha a nis <m>a dhreuchd</m> a
                            leigeil dheth, dh’ iarramaid taing a thoirt dha airson gach seirbhis a
                            thug e do ar cànain, is ghuidheamaid dhà saorsainn is toileachas <m>’na
                                shaorsa</m>, agus obair ás ùr anns na raointean a thaghas e. Anns an
                            aon fhacal chuireamaid fàilte air Fread MacAmhlaidh a tha a’ togail an
                            eallaich. Tha sinn eòlach air a ghuth agus air <m>obair</m>, agus
                            ghuidheamaid gach soirbheachadh leis.</gd>
                        <tr>During the seasons and the years that are ahead of us, it is known that
                            many changes will come to the Gaelic Department of the BBC. Ewan MacPhee
                            has left his own stamp on that Department, and on the BBC in Scotland as
                            a whole, and after him now giving up his job, we would ask for thanks to
                            be given him for all the service he has given to our language, and wish
                            him liberty and pleasure in his freedom, and new work in the areas that
                            he will choose. In the same word we would welcome Fred MacAulay who is
                            taking up the burden. We know his voice and his work, and we would wish
                            him every success.</tr>
                        <ref text="400-48">td. 297, ‘Air an Spiris’</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha beagan airgid aige ’s mar sin chaith e <m>a bheatha</m> a’
                            sgrìobhadh, gun feum aige air obair eile a dhèanamh.</gd>
                        <tr>He had a little money and therefore <u>he</u> devoted <u>his</u> life to
                            writing, without the need to do other work.</tr>
                        <ref text="400-41">td. 103</ref>
                        <note>reflexive ie. himself’s</note>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
